\begin_layout Section
SREP-16-40973: Reply to Reviewer #1
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\color blue
The manuscript reported by Bera et al used Bayesian inference to elucidate
 the optical trap stiffness and the diffusion coefficient of particles within
 the trap.
 The paper presents two Bayesian methods, which do not require Monte Carlo
 sampling, are extremely fast, exact and can serve as an useful “null hypothesis
” when comparing between different models for the data.
 At the end, the manuscript gives some perspective to present Bayesian methods
 for more complex models and provide a fully Bayesian procedure.
 Generally, this paper is well organized and written.
 The manuscript has a certain technical depth and strong logic, but the
 layout of the paper is not good.
 I recommend a major revision.
 
