\begin_layout Itemize

\color blue
The manuscript discusses some limitations of this method.
 For example, “the error bars of the Bayesian estimate for the diffusion
 coefficient, which are higher than that for the k measurement, chiefly
 reflect the systematic errors in our experimental apparatus that may arise
 due to slow drifts of the laser power……”It would be better to do some experimen
ts to explain these problems.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\end_inset


\color inherit
We have performed a whole series of measurements to check for systematic
 errors in our experiments.
 This has been done in two ways: a) by comparing the mean and standard deviation
 of measured trapping parameters over 3 sets of independent time series
 data collected at low and high trapping laser powers for the same particle
 (diameter 3 microns), and b) by comparing the trapping parameters measured
 on time series data of different length obtained at the same laser power
 for the same particle.
 The results are shown in Tables III(a) and (b).
 It is clear that systematics due to coupling with low frequency ambient
 noise occurs for low stiffness traps, while that due to slow drifts in
 experimental conditions occur at time scales longer than 20s.
 A detailed discussion has now been given in pages 6 and 7 of the revision.
\end_layout

