\begin_layout Standard

\color blue
The authors applied two Bayesian methods to the analysis of the Brownian
 motion of a colloid particle confined in an optical trap.
 The trap stiffness and diffusion coefficient can be estimated and compared
 with the best fit to PSD and Stokes-Einstein relation.
 The validity of the methods were then appropriately checked.
 The current Bayesian methods do not require Monte Carlo sampling and are
 very accurate and fast.
 And I personally appreciate the authors’ comments on Bayesian analysis
 in the conclusion part.
 They informed the readers of the great potential of the Bayesian methods
 in soft matter study, which have not been fully explored yet.
 I think this is a rather well-written paper, for the clearly presented
 theoretical and experimental procedures and adequate illustrations.
 I recommend the acceptance.
 But some minor comments may help the manuscript to be finalized: 
