\color blue
I’m wondering whether the Bayesian methods can be applied to study the rotationa
l diffusion and exerted torque constant of a nonspherical particle in optical
 trap.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\end_inset


\color black
We thank the reviewer for raising this important point.
 Bayesian methods can indeed be used to study this important case as well.
 The analysis will be considerably more involved, as there will be a coupling
 of position and orientation, involving the solution of the 6 coupled stochastic
 differential equations (or, a Fokker-Planck equation in 6 variables).
 As analytical solutions are generally not known for arbitrary times, we
 will either have to resort to short time expansions when experimental data
 is collected sufficiently rapidly compared to the typical relaxation times,
 or, fall back on Markov Chain Monte Carlo for the general case.
 We now add this remark in the discussion.
 
\end_layout

